1. Purpose

Interface to the RNS program by N. Stergioulas for rotating 
neutron star initial data.  This is based on version 2.0 as 
publicly available at http://www.gravity.phys.uwm.edu/rns/ .

Thorn written partially while at Tuebingen.

This is still very much in the development phase. The following
are still to be done:

	* Clear up units questions (poly vs general EoS)
	* Add possibility to move NS origin.
	* Test non-polytrope EoS NS.
	* Remove hard-coding of RNS grid resolution.
	* Convert numerical recipes code to GSL code.
